body:
@bolkedebruin it adds about 1-3s to task scheduling.

This is only when scheduling new tasks, not heartbeating. It also applies only to individual DAG schedulers. It's potentially costly if a given DAG has a large number of tasks that need to be scheduled at the same time and the system has a large parallelism limit.

It's a bit of a stopgap for a race condition that we've run into a number of times. Longer term, I'm hoping to do a more thorough rewrite of the executor system but stopgaps solve problems and hopes don't.
